</snippet>

<snippet name="hallOfStatues" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Hall of Statues</h3>

    <p>On both sides of this corridor, overgrown statues sit in regularly placed alcoves, the features of each obscured by white flowers. Piles of waterlogged machinery lie neglected on the floor, some overgrown with white fuzz. The walls are covered in it.</p>

    <p>One alcove is populated by a <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="13">marble plaque</a>.</p>

    <p>Steps descend to a flooded intersection in the [[southwest|floodedHallIntersection]]. To the [[northeast|statueTowerStairwell]], the corridor opens into a stairwell.</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="overgrownStorage" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Overgrown Storage</h3>

    <p>Scattered here and there are metallic crates. Most are overgrown with twisting white vines that disperse at your touch, and reform once you withdraw from them. A <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="17">marble plaque</a> has been nailed onto one of the crates.</p>

    <p>To the [[south|overgrownHallWest]], a rusty door leads to an overgrown hallway.</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="overgrownHallEast" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Overgrown Hall - East</h3>

    <p>A mass of flowers hang from the ceiling of this corridor, pure white against the blue-black stone. White vines twine in and out of the walls. Everywhere is white mist or foliage, constantly dispersing and swirling together. You can't tell the difference between the two. The <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="93">marble plaque</a> on the wall looks misty, irreal.</p>

    <p>The hall runs to the [[east|floodedHallIntersection]], where you hear the sound of running water, and the [[west|overgrownHallWest]]. A stone door stands open to the [[south|overgrownPillar]].</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="overgrownHallGraveyard" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Overgrown Hall - Graveyard</h3>

    <p>The crumpled bodies of robots lie here, overgrown with white flowers. A <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="18">marble plaque</a> floats above one of the larger broken robots: a dismembered android, its one remaining eye encircled by white vines. Vines grow everywhere, twining into the old machines, sprouting from the cracks.</p>

    <p>A stone archway to the [[southwest|greenhouseEntrance]] opens into a larger chamber. The hallway continues to the [[east|overgrownHallWest]].</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="overgrownHallWest" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Overgrown Hall - West</h3>

    <p>This section of the hall is piled with broken machinery: cracked glass bulbs and rusty pipes and buttons of all sorts. Enormous white flowers shine on the ceiling, the walls. Their vines have snaked into every crevice of these old machines. Lights still blink on and off on some, flashing red and green indicators, but no alarm sounds. They are beyond repair.</p>

    <p>A <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="16">marble plaque</a> is set into a wall.</p>

    <p>A rusty door swings to the [[north|overgrownStorage]]. The hall runs to the [[east|overgrownHallEast]] and [[west|overgrownHallGraveyard]].</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="overgrownPillar" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Overgrown Pillar</h3>

    <p>A broken pillar, covered in white vines, stands in the center of this room. Whatever it might have supported is no longer there. A <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="15">marble plaque</a> levitates above the remains of the pillar, rotating slowly.</p>

    <p>To the [[north|overgrownHallEast]], a stone door leads to an overgrown hallway.</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="pit" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="panelFull absoluteAlign hidden" identifier="pitMenu">Will you [[jump|sunkenHallTransition]] into the pit?</div>

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Pit</h3>

    <p>An enormous <span class="hiddenLink"><a class="panelOpener" identifier="pitMenu">pit</a></span> carves this hallway in half. Water rushes into it, cascading into darkness, producing a cacophonous roar. Crossing is impossible. You cannot see the bottom.</p>

    <p>The hall continues to the [[south|collapsedHall]].</p>
</div>
</snippet>

<snippet name="statueTowerStairwell" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="panelFull absoluteAlign hidden" identifier="statues">
    <p>They look more like lumps of stone than statues. Someone has labeled them, all the same:</p>

    <p>The Girl Who Lived In The Reflection of A Glass of Water</p>

    <p>Jostiphenes, the Jester with 1911 Faces</p>

    <p>Angels' Muse</p>

    <p>Blind Pilgrim PÄ“teris, Impaled On His Own Thorns</p>
</div>

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Statue Tower - Stairwell</h3>

    <p>This spiral staircase winds [[up|statueTowerSummit]] a tall stairwell. Water drips from some secret place as you climb. <a class="panelOpener" identifier="statues">Statues</a> protrude from alcoves in the walls, their forms weathered and overgrown by white vines. One statue that might be a blindfolded human is holding a <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="91">marble plaque</a>. Going down [[southwest|hallOfStatues]] takes you to a statue-filled hallway.</p>
</div>
</snippet>


<snippet name="statueTowerSummit" tags="greenhouse">

<div class="absoluteAlign topHalf">
</div>
<div class="absoluteAlign bottomHalf blackBg">
    <h3 class="roomName">Statue Tower - Summit</h3>

    <p>The stone door at the top of the stairwell leads to a flat, circular roof. No parapet keeps you from jumping. Beyond is only mist, pierced through by some flickering florescence that radiates blue light onto the stone. A <a class="whiteMarker marblePlaque" board="14">marble plaque</a> stands guard by the edge.</p>

    <p>The stairs lead [[down|statueTowerStairwell]].</p>
</div>
</snippet>


